    <ab>
                        <lb n="1"/>
                        
                        
                            
                            Ἀσκληπιάδης Μη<lb break="no" n="2"/>νοφἰλου Νεικομηδεύς <lb n="3"/>ὁ καὶ Ἀζανείτης ἔνπο<lb break="no" n="4"/>ρος, Μηνοφίλῳ Βά<supplied reason="lost">σ</supplied> <lb n="5"/><supplied reason="lost">σ</supplied>ῳ ἀδελφῷ, ἐνπόρῳ, <lb n="6"/>καὶ Ἀσκληπιάδης Μη<lb break="no" n="7"/>νοφίλου τῷ πατρί· <lb n="8"/><supplied reason="lost">ἔ</supplied>ζη ἔτη ξ', τὸν βω<lb break="no" n="9"/>μον μνή(μης) χάριν. <lb n="10"/>Χαῖρε παροδεῖτα.
                        
                        
                    </ab>

                
                
            </div>

            
           <div type="translation">
                <p>                    Asklepiades, the son of Menophilos, from Nicomedia and from Aizanoi, trademan, dedicated the altar to the memory of his brother Menophilos the son of Bassus, also trademan; and Asklepiades, the son of Menophilos, dedicated the altar to his father, who lived sixty years. Fare-thee-well, passer-by.</p>
